counter = 0
pets = ["Dog", "Cat", "Fish", "Bird", "Hamster"]
 
while pets[counter] do
  puts pets[counter]
  counter += 1
end

#=> Will output:
Dog
Cat
Fish
Bird
Hamster
This is an example of abstracting array output very basic example a while loop with a counter



def output_array_elements(array)
  counter = 0
 
  while array[counter] do
    puts array[counter]
    counter += 1
  end
end
pets = ["Dog", "Cat", "Fish", "Bird", "Hamster"]
output_array_elements(pets)


def output_array_elements(array)
  counter = 0
 
  while counter < array.length do
    puts array[counter]
    counter += 1
  end
end